1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:17,460
=Episode 9=
(This story is entirely fictional.)

17
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,320
- Drop dead, all of you!
- Drop dead!

18
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,280
- Go to hell!
- Drop dead!

19
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:23,120
- You'll rot in hell!
- Go to hell!

20
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,200
More vegetables?

21
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,080
Whoa, stop!

22
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:27,960
Folks.

23
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,120
What's the grain price

24
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,120
up to now?

25
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,320
330 coins.

26
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,640
330 coins?

27
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,280
It's really shot up, hasn't it?

28
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,400
But it's nearly peaked by now.

29
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,680
Carry on.

30
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:38,880
Keep your shirts on.

31
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,480
You're just unbelievable.

32
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:46,360
Li Yunhe,
if you still call yourself a man,

33
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,080
you'll drag your sorry ass out there

34
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,720
by noon tomorrow.

35
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,320
Don't you drag the trouble
you stirred up

36
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:52,480
onto the Zhou family.

37
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,200
Noon tomorrow, is it?

38
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,280
No big deal.

39
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,960
Right now, every river dock in Feng City

40
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,680
is completely jam-packed

41
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,480
with grain ships.

42
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:01,760
The Marquis House

43
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,520
has bought up all that grain.

44
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,560
The common folk can't get a bite to eat.

45
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,680
No grain?
Then they can just skip a few meals.

46
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,080
Call it a crash diet.

47
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,120
Fancy some tea?

48
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,680
You're still in the mood for tea?

49
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,880
The fury outside these walls
is boiling over.

50
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,360
Are you not the slightest bit worried?

51
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,320
Seems like you're starting to regret

52
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:20,000
not throwing me out
of the Zhou household sooner.

53
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,880
Don't worry.

54
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,880
I'll remember this kindness of yours.

55
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,560
Once all this blows over,

56
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,720
when there's money to be made,

57
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,080
I'll cut you in.

58
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,000
Alright?

59
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:28,880
You're insane.

60
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:31,080
You and Zhou Xingyu
have both gone stark raving mad.

61
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,680
Before noon tomorrow, correct?

62
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,720
If the situation hasn't been
resolved by then,

63
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,280
I will leave the Zhou Manor
of my own accord.

64
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,520
When that time comes,

65
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:42,600
I hope you won't
make things hard for Yu.

66
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,880
Hope you're a man of your word.

67
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,800
Oh, right.

68
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,600
Help me pass a message
to the government office, will you?

69
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,160
So what's that live-in son-in-law

70
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,280
been up to?

71
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,440
Your Majesty,

72
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,280
Mr. Li has been lazing about at home,

73
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,520
whiling away the time with tea.

74
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,880
Now and then, he climbs the wall

75
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,560
to chat with the folks outside

76
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:02,080
and collects some rotten cabbages.

77
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,720
Amusing. Highly amusing.

78
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,520
There must be more than dozens
of people outside the Zhou Manor

79
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,200
who want him dead.

80
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,280
And he still has the nerve
to poke his head over the wall

81
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,120
and shoot the breeze
about everyday trifles.

82
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,000
But

83
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,400
why do I get the feeling

84
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,400
that he somehow

85
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,880
has victory in the bag?

86
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:23,080
Yunzhuo, tell me,

87
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,360
could it be that this habit of his,

88
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,160
climbing the wall every few days,

89
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,720
means he's sounding out
public sentiment?

90
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,800
Did you actually see him

91
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,600
sounding out public sentiment?

92
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,720
If the Zhou Manor
hadn't been frantically

93
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,800
handing out porridge
and grain these past few days,

94
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,040
the common folk

95
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,760
would have probably
already stormed that manor by now.

96
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,280
And the way things are going

97
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,760
won't hold out much longer.

98
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,280
I bet he'll be fine.

99
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,040
Whether he's fine or not,

100
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,880
isn't that just a matter
of a single word from me?

101
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:50,760
Give him a hand.

102
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,280
Don't give me that.

103
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,800
I've already sunk a fortune into this.

104
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,440
But the grain price

105
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,800
is still staying stubbornly high.

106
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,680
Public fury is boiling.

107
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:01,000
The fact
that I haven't torn him limb from limb

108
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:01,880
is already

109
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,280
the greatest mercy I can show him.

110
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:10,920
Your Majesty,

111
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,720
this is the letter
the Zhou household sent out.

112
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,280
Both the Prefect's Office
and we received a copy.

113
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,920
Prepare a proclamation at once.

114
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,400
Issue it tomorrow morning.

115
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,480
Announce that disaster relief grain
from the capital has arrived.

116
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,960
The government will open its granaries
and distribute grain,

117
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,680
which can resolve the current disaster.

118
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:31,840
Tomorrow?

119
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,560
The relief grain from the capital

120
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,920
can't possibly arrive that quickly,
can it?

121
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,520
He merely wants
to borrow the government's authority

122
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,320
to pacify the people one more time.

123
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,720
But still,

124
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:43,120
it's just stalling his doom a bit,
that's all.

125
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,120
Hold on.

126
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,280
Relief grain arrives.

127
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,680
The government opens granaries
and distributes grain.

128
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,320
Now I see.

129
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,800
What a genius. A sheer genius!

130
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:00,120
Read me what Li Yunhe

131
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,480
wrote in the letter.

132
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,160
(Sell)
Just one word, Your Majesty. Sell.

133
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,720
Even at a loss,

134
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,720
sell every last grain

135
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,800
to the Marquis House.

136
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,160
Understood.

137
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,280
(Zhou Manor)
Li Yunhe, get your ass out here!

138
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:21,080
- Out!
- Get out here!

139
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,560
- Li Yunhe, get your ass out here!
- Come out!

140
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,880
- Get out here!
- Li Yunhe, get out here now!

141
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,080
Li Yunhe,

142
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,800
how dare you
still have the gall to be asleep!

143
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,880
Throw him out this instant!

144
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,240
Don't touch me.

145
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,600
I said don't touch me!

146
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,240
Let go of me!

147
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,240
Let him go.

148
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:38,800
All of you, leave us.

149
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:42,800
Huaijin, what are you doing?

150
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,360
Even now, you're still protecting him?

151
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,560
He started everything.

152
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,120
Look at the Zhou household.

153
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,440
See what it's been reduced to?

154
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,600
Enough bickering.

155
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,760
What time is it now?

156
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,160
It's noon right now.

157
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,400
Noon has come.

158
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:55,520
Alright.

159
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,440
Chunxiang.

160
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,960
Have the folks outside dispersed yet?

161
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,160
Some left earlier on,

162
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,600
but now quite a crowd
has gathered again,

163
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,760
and it's growing bigger and bigger.

164
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,560
It seems

165
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,800
it's time for me to go out
and take a little stroll.

166
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:11,920
No.

167
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,280
I won't allow you to go out there.

168
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,400
Relax.

169
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,040
Nothing's going to happen to me.

170
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:24,960
Get back here!

171
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,080
Since ancient times,

172
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,400
heroes have always had to

173
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,360
shoulder some misunderstandings.

174
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,160
And at this very moment,

175
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,200
I'm already

176
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,280
standing at

177
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,560
the crossroads of destiny.

178
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,280
Li Yunhe, come back!

179
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,480
Don't you go out there!

180
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,240
Li Yunhe!

181
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,040
Let go of me!

182
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,160
What are you doing?

183
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:41,000
Li Yunhe! Li Yunhe!

184
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,360
Don't you open that gate!

185
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,560
- Get out here!
- Out!

186
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,960
- Get out here!
- Li Yunhe, get your ass out here!

187
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:52,960
(Whether it's an everlasting good name
or eternal infamy,)

188
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,480
(I'll shoulder it all.)

189
00:06:55,480 --> 00:07:04,280
- Li Yunhe, get out here!
- Get out here!

190
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,080
Li Yunhe!

191
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,560
Don't you open that gate!

192
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:13,280
- Get out here!
- Li Yunhe, get out here!

193
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,360
Hold on.

194
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,600
What's the meaning of this?

195
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,680
Didn't you say
you're fond of cabbage, sir?

196
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,640
So, we've brought you another one.

197
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,000
Forgive us, Mr. Li.

198
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,600
We had you all wrong earlier on.

199
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,400
Never imagined you were the one

200
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,640
really looking out for us.

201
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,040
Sir,

202
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,480
I was a fool before,

203
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,640
cursing you with the foulest words.

204
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,160
Could you be the bigger man?

205
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,840
For the Zhous
to have a son-in-law like you,

206
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,840
one who truly cares
for the common people,

207
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,160
that is their greatest blessing.

208
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,560
Please. This is too much.

209
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,400
Please get up.

210
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,360
Wait, ma'am,

211
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,960
what's the grain price situation now?

212
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,880
The government has
started disaster relief.

213
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:54,960
His Majesty

214
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,680
has sent
another shipment of relief grain.

215
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:57,760
Right now, on the market,

216
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,440
there are way too many people
selling grain.

217
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,400
The grain price has plummeted too fast.

218
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,480
I just heard

219
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,800
it's dropped again.

220
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,760
Five coins for a hodful.

221
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,880
Five coins?

222
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,280
Not bad.

223
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,400
Everyone here

224
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,000
can finally have enough grain
to eat now, right?

225
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,000
When you get the chance,

226
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,240
you must give your full support

227
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,680
to the Zhou family's Gambiered Silk,

228
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:15,560
alright?

229
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:15,920
- We will, of course.
- It's only right.

230
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:16,760
We'll support

231
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,160
the Zhous' business for sure.

232
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:19,760
With grain prices this low now,

233
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,840
we definitely have to support
our benefactor's business.

234
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,160
Alright, that's good to hear.

235
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:23,840
Sir.

236
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,080
- This is from my brother. Take it.
- It's for you.

237
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:27,040
- Oh, this really isn't necessary.
- Just take it.

238
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,680
- That's enough.
- Take it, sir.

239
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,480
That's plenty.

240
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,560
How could this happen?

241
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,960
What did Mr. Li do?

242
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:35,840
How did things

243
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,400
turn out this way?

244
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:40,620
(Grain Price: 5 coins per hodful)

245
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,280
Today's grain price is

246
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,560
five coins for a hodful.

247
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:45,900
(Xinfeng Grain Shop)
Wow, so cheap.

248
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:46,960
- Five coins per hodful?
- That's cheap.

249
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,680
- It's 5 coins per hodful today!
- Wow!

250
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,880
- All thanks to Li Yunhe!
- Wonderful!

251
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,120
Li Yunhe is truly

252
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,200
- our greatest benefactor!
- All thanks to him.

253
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,500
- Wonderful!
- Let's go.

254
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,920
Give me some of that.

255
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,700
Wow, what a bargain!

256
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:01,880
Here you go.

257
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,960
The public fury has been quelled?

258
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,680
That's wonderful.

259
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,160
Li Yunhe won't have to die now,

260
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,760
and our family is safe, too.

261
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:20,840
My lady!

262
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:24,000
- My lady!
- Yu!

263
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,080
Doctor,

264
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,160
how is she?

265
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,240
It's nothing serious.

266
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,960
She's just been
overworking herself lately.

267
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,360
A bit of rest and she'll be alright.

268
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:49,360
That's a relief.

269
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,760
Thank you, doctor.

270
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,680
Chunxiang.

271
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,080
Help me look after Yu.

272
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:03,760
I need to go out for a bit.

273
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,080
Where are you going, Mr. Li?

274
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,200
To collect some money.

275
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:16,760
(Xianquan Tavern)

276
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,960
(Xianquan Tavern)
This Feng City Prefect

277
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,360
is quite a character.

278
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,240
We thought

279
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:22,080
we might need to
give him a little nudge.

280
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:22,960
But who'd have guessed

281
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:23,840
he'd actually follow

282
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,240
Li Yunhe's plan to the letter?

283
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,600
When it concerns the people's livelihood

284
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,000
and his own official post,

285
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,400
of course he'd cooperate fully.

286
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:31,920
It seems I still

287
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,800
underestimated
Li Yunhe's boldness of vision.

288
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,960
What are the people saying?

289
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:40,000
Earlier, when the Prefect
issued the proclamation,

290
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,640
afraid of taking the blame,

291
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,640
he stated it was

292
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:45,160
the scheme of the folk prodigy Li Yunhe.

293
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,960
Now, all the citizens across the city

294
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,000
have come to realize

295
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,600
it was Mr. Li's doing.

296
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,480
His reputation is rising greatly.

297
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,160
So his reputation is soaring.

298
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,120
The Marquis House,

299
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,840
on the other hand,
has been completely screwed over.

300
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,240
I'm rather curious,

301
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,040
how will the Marquis's heir

302
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,600
deal with him now?

303
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,200
Behead him!

304
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,600
Drag him out and behead him!

305
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,580
- My lord, calm down.
- Please, calm down.

306
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:12,680
Calm down?

307
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,680
The Marquis House's entire fortune

308
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,560
is gone.

309
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,200
330 coins per hodful was the price

310
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,160
we bought the grain at.

311
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,560
Now it's worth a measly three coins.

312
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:25,060
How can I calm down?

313
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,440
You tell me!

314
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,560
We had no way of knowing

315
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,520
that the court's disaster relief grain

316
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,040
would arrive so quickly.

317
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,360
My lord,

318
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:35,240
relief grain traveled all the way
from the capital to Feng City.

319
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,160
Such a vast distance

320
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:36,880
and so quickly?

321
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,800
This has to be fake news.

322
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,760
What the hell do I pay you two for?

323
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,160
Who issued that government proclamation?

324
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,160
Couldn't you
have tipped me off in advance?

325
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,160
The docks are packed
to the brim with grain ships.

326
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:52,960
Whether the court's relief grain

327
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,240
has arrived or not,

328
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,440
we can't tell them apart at all.

329
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:58,760
It's just... My lord,

330
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,280
the grain prices
were soaring too fiercely.

331
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,200
The Prefect probably
couldn't withstand the pressure

332
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,440
and put out fake news

333
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,200
to confuse us.

334
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,160
He couldn't withstand it,

335
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,880
so I have to take the fall?

336
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:07,400
My lord,

337
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:08,560
everything that happened

338
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,360
is all Li Yunhe's fault.

339
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,160
That's right.

340
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:12,960
If it weren't for Li Yunhe

341
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,760
feeding the government
this rotten scheme,

342
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:15,360
things would never

343
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,320
have ended up like this.

344
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,160
Exactly.

345
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,200
Good.

346
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,160
Very good indeed.

347
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,240
Li Yunhe

348
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,760
has dug

349
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:28,400
a massive trap for me,

350
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,000
causing my Marquis House

351
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,360
to lose every last ounce

352
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,360
of ready silver in this grain war.

353
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,840
He'll be so sorry.

354
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,200
My lord,

355
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:41,280
what should we do next?

356
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,360
Our granaries are already overflowing.

357
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,920
There are still grain merchants outside

358
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,760
waiting to sell us their grain.

359
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,800
Do I need to spell this out for you?

360
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,440
Make those who sold me grain
at a high price earlier

361
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,440
refund the money!

362
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,160
But if we do that,

363
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,680
the Marquis House's reputation...

364
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,040
What darn use is reputation?

365
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:03,800
My money...

366
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,240
They earn 300 coins per hodful,

367
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,760
and what do I earn?

368
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:10,880
I told you not to buy grain,

369
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,560
but you just had to
recklessly hoard it all.

370
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,000
Now that the price has collapsed,

371
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:16,040
who's going to eat all this grain
you've stockpiled?

372
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:17,600
Please calm down, my lord.

373
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,360
We didn't see this coming either.

374
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,320
How could such a golden opportunity

375
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,760
turn out like this?

376
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,880
I told you to go help
the disaster victims earlier.

377
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,960
Now that the grain price has crashed,

378
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,200
what disaster victims are even left?

379
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:29,480
What a disaster.

380
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,960
The grain is going to rot
in the granaries.

381
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,360
What a catastrophe.

382
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,280
My lord,
then what about the money we lost?

383
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,160
Still yammering about money?

384
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:45,160
I need to go find Li Yunhe right now

385
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:47,480
and get this batch of grain
off our hands.

386
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,160
If it rots in the granaries,

387
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,640
the Xie family's name

388
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,040
will be completely ruined.

389
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,040
Sir, Li Yunhe requests an audience.

390
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:43,840
Zhuo, how goes it?

391
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,000
Did you make a killing?

392
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,000
Just like we agreed beforehand,

393
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,680
a fifty-fifty split.

394
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:54,880
Oh, Zhuo, don't tell me

395
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,200
you're planning to renege?

396
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,880
Li Yunhe, you've got some nerve!

397
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:00,560
Do you even know

398
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,840
who you're talking to right now?

399
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,560
Do you know who you're talking to?

400
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,360
Sit down!

401
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:11,080
Hey, I'll admit it,

402
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,560
this fifty-fifty split

403
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:13,960
really is a bit much.

404
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,640
But look, in business,

405
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,000
it's all about
playing the information gap.

406
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:18,840
Without me, the mastermind

407
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,440
pulling the strings behind the scenes,

408
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,560
you couldn't have raked in
this much cash.

409
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,480
Am I right?

410
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,240
I thought you'd forgotten

411
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,840
that you're trying to make something
out of thin air.

412
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,240
Well, you've got a point there.

413
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:33,240
But wasn't it you who proposed

414
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,760
this fifty-fifty split
in the first place?

415
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:35,960
Are you sure?

416
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:11,900
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

417
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:15,260
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

418
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:18,500
♪Who took the March rain♪

419
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:22,100
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

420
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:25,260
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

421
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:28,620
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

422
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:35,420
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

423
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:38,900
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

424
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:41,980
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

425
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:44,420
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

426
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:48,620
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

427
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:51,980
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

428
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:55,260
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

429
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:58,700
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

430
00:16:58,860 --> 00:17:05,380
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

431
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:35,180
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

432
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:38,580
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

433
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:41,900
♪Who took the March rain♪

434
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:45,420
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

435
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:48,700
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

436
00:17:48,780 --> 00:17:52,500
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

437
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:55,820
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

438
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:58,780
♪As seasons change♪

439
00:17:58,780 --> 00:18:02,420
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

440
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:05,260
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

441
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:07,900
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

442
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:11,980
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

443
00:18:11,980 --> 00:18:15,300
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

444
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:19,020
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

445
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:22,540
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

446
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:25,420
♪Only for you♪

447
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:29,020
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

448
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:31,900
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

449
00:18:32,020 --> 00:18:34,580
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

450
00:18:34,580 --> 00:18:38,660
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

451
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:41,980
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

452
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:45,380
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

453
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:51,900
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

454
00:18:52,980 --> 00:18:57,100
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

455
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:02,900
♪Your wedding gown♪
